 _J_a_t_o_x_ _J_a_n_e [Žena] [Kategorie]
31.12.2010 13:20:13
fgj:
No, ono v tom citátu (Lord Acton) myslím nejde o korupci penězi.
Celý je:
"I cannot accept your canon that we are to judge Pope and King unlike other
men with a favourable presumption that they did no wrong. If there is any
presumption, it is the other way, against the holders of power, increasing as
the power increases. Historic responsibility has to make up for the want of
legal responsibility. Power tends to corrupt, and absolute power corrupts
absolutely. Great men are almost always bad men, even when they exercise
influence and not authority: still more when you superadd the tendency or
certainty of corruption by full authority. There is no worse heresy than the
fact that the office sanctifies the holder of it. "
